Vendored copy of `OpenZeppelin/uniswap-hooks` at tag v1.1.0
(https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/uniswap-hooks/releases/tag/v1.1.0,
commit `e59fe72`; last audit-relevant delta at commit `2678eb9`).

Files vendored under this directory:
  * BaseDynamicAfterFee.sol   (src/fee/BaseDynamicAfterFee.sol)
  * BaseHook.sol              (src/base/BaseHook.sol)
  * CurrencySettler.sol       (src/utils/CurrencySettler.sol)
  * IHookEvents.sol           (src/interfaces/IHookEvents.sol)

License: MIT (see ./LICENSE and the copyright notices retained in each
vendored .sol file).

Why vendored:
This case (`experiments/uniswap-v4-invariants/src/cases/p2-dynamicfee-
direction-integrity`) subclasses OpenZeppelin's actual audited
`BaseDynamicAfterFee` to teach the direction-blind fee-arithmetic bug
that `2678eb9` remediated (the finding recorded as M-01 in the OZ
Uniswap Hooks v1.1.0 RC 2 audit). Vendoring the four files here (with
internal sibling imports rewritten to `./` paths) lets the case's
clean twin BE the audited fixed contract, byte-faithful in the
fee-arithmetic block, while leaving the other five cases untouched.

Patches applied to the vendored files (delta from upstream v1.1.0):
  1. Internal `src/<subdir>/*.sol` imports rewritten to `./*.sol`
     sibling imports (BaseHook, CurrencySettler, IHookEvents).
  2. `SwapParams` / `ModifyLiquidityParams` are imported from
     `v4-core/src/types/PoolOperation.sol` (byte-faithful to
     upstream v1.1.0, which imports the same). The v4-core pin
     (`^1.0.2`, matching the OZ hooks package.json declaration)
     carries `PoolOperation.sol`, so no local rewrite is needed.
     No fee-arithmetic block was altered.
  3. `openzeppelin/utils/*` and `openzeppelin/token/*` imports left
     unchanged; the top-level foundry.toml carries a case-scoped
     `openzeppelin/=` remapping into
     `lib/openzeppelin-uniswap-hooks/lib/openzeppelin-contracts/contracts/`
     so the same source paths resolve.

The audited fee-arithmetic block on lines 155-174 of
`BaseDynamicAfterFee.sol` (branching on `exactInput` and computing
`feeAmount = unspecified - target` for exactInput vs
`feeAmount = target - unspecified` for exactOutput) is copied
character-for-character from the upstream v1.1.0 file.

Reviewer check: a byte-level diff against
`lib/openzeppelin-uniswap-hooks/src/fee/BaseDynamicAfterFee.sol` at
tag `v1.1.0` will show the three patch classes listed above and
nothing else in the fee-arithmetic block.
